<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="536" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1028</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-17">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s 16th. Adjudication by prize-claims committee does not
                                supplant remedy provided in Order V, rule 2, of prize court rules.
                                Committee considers exclusively equity claims of ship repairers,
                                mortgagees and like against ships or cargoes already finally dealt
                                with by prize court, who are deprived of ordinary remedies and
                                cannot appear in ordinary proceedings.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>